170
00:15:24,257 --> 00:15:27,058
              Now, Nurse, if you
              are to be with us

171
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:30,895
          I must ask that
          you put aside any
        preconditioned attitudes

172
00:15:30,897 --> 00:15:33,431
          you may have
          as to the treatment
          of the insane.

173
00:15:33,433 --> 00:15:39,304
  Oh, Dr. Quilly, a man
  with your reputation doesn't
  have to explain originality.

174
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:43,775
        Well, our theories
        are deceptively simple.

175
00:15:43,777 --> 00:15:45,743
            Our guests...

176
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:48,079
       Well, they have fantasies
        that are not accepted

177
00:15:48,081 --> 00:15:52,383
      in the so-called
      outside, real, sane world.

178
00:15:52,385 --> 00:15:57,322
        But here, under extreme
        controlled situations,

179
00:15:57,324 --> 00:15:59,991
          we allow them to
         act out their fantasies

180
00:15:59,993 --> 00:16:01,659
                as if they were
                totally sane.

181
00:16:01,661 --> 00:16:04,796
      Yes. I met some of
      your guests earlier.

182
00:16:04,798 --> 00:16:08,132
        And we have found
        that if they get to
       exercise these fantasies,

183
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:11,836
          after a time they
          no longer need them.

184
00:16:11,838 --> 00:16:13,304
            Now, I realize
            that takes a while,

185
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,307
          but there are no
          sudden therapies
          for the mad,

186
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:19,410
              so here
              at the Institute
              no one is mad.

187
00:16:21,915 --> 00:16:24,849
                Uh, would you
                be willing to
               dress as a nurse?

188
00:16:24,851 --> 00:16:26,884
  That's your prerogative.

189
00:16:29,089 --> 00:16:32,156
  I really want
  this opportunity.

190
00:16:32,158 --> 00:16:34,292
                Then I take it,
                Miss Manning,

191
00:16:34,294 --> 00:16:38,162
      that you are prepared
      to commit to the Institute
      and all its values?

192
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:41,632
      Not only to the Institute,
      but to all its people.

193
00:16:41,634 --> 00:16:43,034
                  Ah!

194
00:16:43,837 --> 00:16:46,637
          Now I really believe
          you understand us.

195
00:16:46,639 --> 00:16:49,173
          However, I will
          need a commitment.

196
00:16:50,276 --> 00:16:51,676
              Your commitment.

197
00:16:51,678 --> 00:16:53,678
            You have it.

198
00:16:54,381 --> 00:16:56,681
                  Done and done.

199
00:16:56,683 --> 00:17:00,385
      There is, I'm afraid,
      some boring paper work.

200
00:17:00,387 --> 00:17:06,624
    Your withholding thing,
    your RN registration number
    and more ad nauseam.

201
00:17:06,626 --> 00:17:09,961
    Such a gigantic bureaucracy
    for such a small formality.

202
00:17:09,963 --> 00:17:11,462
  It's just as bad at home.

203
00:17:11,464 --> 00:17:14,499
      Ms. Donnymead will fill in
      all the details

204
00:17:14,501 --> 00:17:18,269
   from that letter you sent us.
   Why don't you just sign here?

205
00:17:19,739 --> 00:17:23,207
          Ms. Donnymead's
        swamped with paper work.

206
00:17:28,381 --> 00:17:31,382
      I can't tell you
      how excited I am.

207
00:17:31,384 --> 00:17:34,685
  Uh, do you have
  a phone that I could use?
  Collect, of course.

208
00:17:34,687 --> 00:17:38,256
  I want to call my family
  and tell them I'm all right,

209
00:17:38,258 --> 00:17:41,859
      very all right,
      productive again.

210
00:17:41,861 --> 00:17:46,030
          I'm sorry,
          I'm afraid we
          cannot have that.

211
00:17:46,032 --> 00:17:47,732
  I promise it's collect.

212
00:17:48,935 --> 00:17:52,870
      Miss Manning,
      you are not ready yet

213
00:17:52,872 --> 00:17:57,575
        to upset your
        family and friends,
        not at all ready.

214
00:17:57,577 --> 00:18:00,945
    Don't forget you have
    just committed yourself.

215
00:18:00,947 --> 00:18:04,248
  I beg your pardon?
  Did you say committed?

216
00:18:05,618 --> 00:18:07,452
  No, I'm here as a nurse.

217
00:18:07,454 --> 00:18:11,355
          Of course you are.
          You are whatever
          you say you are.

218
00:18:11,357 --> 00:18:14,092
        Don't you remember?
        I told you about
        our theories

219
00:18:14,094 --> 00:18:16,694
          and you said you
          would commit to us.

220
00:18:16,696 --> 00:18:21,365
    I meant committed
    in an entirely
    different context.

221
00:18:21,367 --> 00:18:23,367
          I'm a nurse.

222
00:18:23,369 --> 00:18:26,070
        A real nurse.

223
00:18:26,072 --> 00:18:29,140
            If you want
            to be a nurse,
            be a nurse.

