284
00:25:25,658 --> 00:25:27,157
          Why did you
          commit yourself?

285
00:25:27,159 --> 00:25:28,659
        I didn't!

286
00:25:28,661 --> 00:25:32,129
  He handed me a form and
  he said that Ms. Donny...

287
00:25:32,131 --> 00:25:34,131
  Whatever the hell her name is,

288
00:25:34,133 --> 00:25:35,699
    would fill in the details.

289
00:25:35,701 --> 00:25:38,669
      Are you in the habit
      of signing blank forms?

290
00:25:38,671 --> 00:25:41,071
    Of course I'm not
    in the habit of
    signing blank forms.

291
00:25:41,073 --> 00:25:44,642
  It just seemed so routine.
  We spoke on the phone.

292
00:25:44,644 --> 00:25:46,043
    I was desperate
    for the job and...

293
00:25:46,045 --> 00:25:47,411
              Desperate?

294
00:25:50,182 --> 00:25:52,349
  Will you please help me?

295
00:25:52,351 --> 00:25:54,051
          I'd like very much
          to help you.

296
00:25:54,053 --> 00:25:58,722
  They put me in
  a basement room.

297
00:25:58,724 --> 00:26:01,258
          Basement room?
          Can you take us there?

298
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:03,360
  No, I can't take you there.
  I don't know how I got there

299
00:26:03,362 --> 00:26:05,329
  and I don't know
  who put me there.

300
00:26:05,331 --> 00:26:07,865
            Basement room?

301
00:26:07,867 --> 00:26:09,867
            But there is
            no basement room

302
00:26:09,869 --> 00:26:12,603
          or anything like
          a basement room
          in this institute.

303
00:26:12,605 --> 00:26:14,605
        Is there, Dr. Moore?

304
00:26:14,607 --> 00:26:16,106
                  No.

305
00:26:18,377 --> 00:26:20,177
        It's somewhere.

306
00:26:20,179 --> 00:26:22,780
          Yes. It is somewhere.

307
00:26:24,050 --> 00:26:25,749
              In the mind.

308
00:26:27,453 --> 00:26:30,554
      In whose mind,
      Dr. Quilly?

309
00:26:30,556 --> 00:26:32,356
      Yours or mine?

310
00:26:45,738 --> 00:26:47,137
  (MAN MOANS)

311
00:26:55,047 --> 00:26:57,748
           You're the new nurse.

312
00:26:57,750 --> 00:27:00,317
               My name is David.

313
00:27:00,319 --> 00:27:02,086
            David means beloved.

314
00:27:02,088 --> 00:27:05,789
  Actually, it means
  beloved king.

315
00:27:06,892 --> 00:27:10,260
                I'm no king.
                I'm no one.

316
00:27:10,262 --> 00:27:12,062
          No.

317
00:27:12,064 --> 00:27:14,465
  Everyone is someone.

318
00:27:16,602 --> 00:27:18,502
    Why are you
    locked up?

319
00:27:18,504 --> 00:27:21,138
            They never told me.

320
00:27:21,140 --> 00:27:23,273
              They just feed me.

321
00:27:23,275 --> 00:27:25,776
                And someone
               comes to wash me.

322
00:27:25,778 --> 00:27:28,445
                      I used to
                    wash myself.

323
00:27:28,447 --> 00:27:31,448
                I used to
                laugh and wash,

324
00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:35,252
            but now they
           never bring me sweets
            after feeding me.

325
00:27:35,254 --> 00:27:40,624
          After dinner could you
          bring me a sweet
          or anything? Please.

326
00:27:40,626 --> 00:27:42,326
        Of course.

327
00:27:42,328 --> 00:27:44,028
                Thank you.

328
00:27:44,964 --> 00:27:47,498
            You won't let them
            kill you, will you?

329
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:49,767
          They'll try, you know?

330
00:27:49,769 --> 00:27:52,436
            They like to
            kill nurses here.

331
00:27:52,438 --> 00:27:55,056
          Why...

332
00:27:55,057 --> 00:27:57,675
                  If I could,
                I would help you
                  fly away home.

333
00:27:57,677 --> 00:27:59,109
                    But I can't.

334
00:28:00,179 --> 00:28:02,713
      You won't forget my sweet.

335
00:28:02,715 --> 00:28:04,782
            Means a lot to me.

336
00:28:04,784 --> 00:28:06,116
          No.

337
00:31:11,303 --> 00:31:14,238
      <i> PAUL: It's a</i>
      <i> fantastic opportunity</i>
      <i> for you, Susan.</i>

338
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:17,140
           <i> Dr. Magnus Quilly</i>
           <i> is a legend.</i>

339
00:31:19,245 --> 00:31:21,578
    <i> Nothing makes any sense.</i>

340
00:31:25,317 --> 00:31:28,752
    <i> I can't do this anymore.</i>

341
00:31:28,754 --> 00:31:30,654
        <i> I want you to leave.</i>

342
00:32:19,738 --> 00:32:21,104
          (KNOCKING AT DOOR)

343
00:32:26,378 --> 00:32:29,846
  I'm sorry.
  We wanted to tell you
