703
00:55:32,930 --> 00:55:34,530
          Go to your rooms!

704
00:55:45,376 --> 00:55:48,344
          You fucking slime!

705
00:55:48,346 --> 00:55:51,580
      I'm gonna slit
      your belly open
      like a flapping fish.

706
00:55:52,383 --> 00:55:54,416
              (PANTING)

707
00:56:03,828 --> 00:56:04,927
          Damn!

708
00:56:08,833 --> 00:56:10,866
    Fucking pig!
            Wait a minute!

709
00:56:10,868 --> 00:56:12,901
        I'll cut your
        goddamn throat!

710
00:56:38,329 --> 00:56:40,863
           <i> SUSAN: "There is a</i>
           <i> chance for escape.</i>

711
00:56:40,865 --> 00:56:43,031
         <i> "A journey that</i>
         <i> you can make.</i>

712
00:56:43,033 --> 00:56:45,167
         <i> "Come and see me</i>
         <i> in the tower.</i>

713
00:56:45,169 --> 00:56:47,903
       <i> "Come at once,</i>
       <i> before it's too late.</i>

714
00:56:47,905 --> 00:56:50,372
         <i> "I wish you well</i>
         <i> in the dark.</i>

715
00:56:50,374 --> 00:56:55,277
  <i> "For the Institute is a place</i>
  <i> where hyenas speak</i>
  <i> and humans bark.</i>

716
00:56:55,279 --> 00:56:56,845
              <i> "Isandra."</i>

717
00:58:38,382 --> 00:58:39,548
                      No!

718
00:59:33,671 --> 00:59:36,238
        Dr. Moore.

719
00:59:36,240 --> 00:59:38,707
  Last night
  before I found Isandra,

720
00:59:38,709 --> 00:59:41,443
  I went to David's room
  and his door was unlocked,

721
00:59:41,445 --> 00:59:43,211
  and he wasn't there.

722
00:59:43,213 --> 00:59:47,282
      I saw David earlier
      this morning. He was in
      his room, peaceful, quiet.

723
00:59:47,284 --> 00:59:49,318
      He wasn't in his
      room last night.

724
00:59:50,588 --> 00:59:52,788
    Can we discuss this later?

725
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:59,561
      Jones, would you, uh,
    ask one of the staff members

726
00:59:59,563 --> 01:00:02,798
    to bring out some candles
    and the fancy table cloths?

727
01:00:02,800 --> 01:00:06,969
        We're gonna
        have a little service.
        She deserves a service.

728
01:00:06,971 --> 01:00:08,704
            JONES:
           I'll take care of it.

729
01:00:21,085 --> 01:00:23,385
       Hi. You've gotta help me.

730
01:00:23,387 --> 01:00:26,054
    See, I came here as a nurse,
     I had credentials, but they
      took my credentials

731
01:00:26,056 --> 01:00:28,724
                  and they say
                  I'm a patient,
                  but I'm not.

732
01:00:31,128 --> 01:00:33,328
          Please, you've
          gotta help me.

733
01:00:33,330 --> 01:00:35,931
      Uh, yeah, we understand.
      Listen, ma'am, why don't
      you talk to Dr. Quilly?

734
01:00:35,933 --> 01:00:39,568
  He'll, uh... He'll give you
  all the help you need.
  Excuse me.

735
01:00:39,570 --> 01:00:40,702
                      But...

736
01:00:56,620 --> 01:00:59,521
        I've been watching you
        get out of hand, Nurse,

737
01:00:59,523 --> 01:01:00,956
          and I've been
          patient long enough.

738
01:01:00,958 --> 01:01:04,026
       There will be punishment,
        severe punishment!

739
01:01:07,297 --> 01:01:09,031
        I'll handle this, Jones.

740
01:01:09,033 --> 01:01:10,766
        But, Dr. Moore,
        the nurse has been
        breaking all our rules!

741
01:01:10,768 --> 01:01:13,001
        How the hell am I
        supposed to keep
        order around here?

742
01:01:13,003 --> 01:01:15,037
              You're doing a
            splendid job, Jones.

743
01:01:15,039 --> 01:01:17,272
            Why don't you
            help the others in?
            Go ahead.

744
01:01:21,779 --> 01:01:23,812
      JONES: All right,
      let's go. Back inside.

745
01:01:23,814 --> 01:01:26,381
      Okay, everyone
      back inside. Let's go.

746
01:01:38,696 --> 01:01:41,196
  SUSAN:
  Isandra told me
  a way to escape.

747
01:01:42,399 --> 01:01:44,399
  Now, I know what
  she really meant.

748
01:01:44,401 --> 01:01:47,302
  There's only one way
  to leave the Institute.

749
01:02:29,012 --> 01:02:31,947
                  Henry seems to
                  do him better
                than the others.

750
01:02:35,886 --> 01:02:39,688
      You know, I have to admit,
      my ego is slightly dented.

751
01:02:39,690 --> 01:02:42,090
            Henry has literally
            never done me.

752
01:02:42,092 --> 01:02:45,393
  Maybe that's because you're
  not the real Dr. Quilly.

753
01:02:45,395 --> 01:02:47,863
                  Now, now,
                  you mustn't
                  mumble, Nurse.

754
01:02:47,865 --> 01:02:50,465
                We can't hear
                what you say,
                we can't help.

755
01:02:52,603 --> 01:02:55,437
    You didn't help Isandra,
    and you heard her.

756
01:02:55,439 --> 01:02:59,040
        You made her speak
        loud and clear and
        everybody listened.

757
01:02:59,042 --> 01:03:00,776
      You knew they would laugh.

758
01:03:02,412 --> 01:03:04,913
  The theory worked.

759
01:03:04,915 --> 01:03:07,916
  Isandra did
  become the poet

760
01:03:07,918 --> 01:03:10,786
  and the poet
  was released
  from the Institute.

761
01:03:12,723 --> 01:03:17,459
            Are you suggesting
            my responsibility
            for Isandra's death?

762
01:03:19,563 --> 01:03:21,663
            Is that what you're
            saying, Dr. Moore?

763
01:03:22,733 --> 01:03:24,666
            I demand an answer.

764
01:03:24,668 --> 01:03:27,736
  Not here, Doctor.
  We have patients here.

765
01:03:30,240 --> 01:03:35,577
      Jones, Ms. Donnymead,
    Lucille, see our guests out.

766
01:03:36,780 --> 01:03:39,514
            This meal is over!

767
01:03:42,019 --> 01:03:45,187
                You too, Nurse,
                may be excused.

768
01:03:48,959 --> 01:03:50,759
          (BELL RINGING)

769
01:04:06,176 --> 01:04:10,045
  How dare you
  question me in public?

770
01:04:10,047 --> 01:04:12,147
              I asked you
            not to make a scene.

771
01:04:12,149 --> 01:04:14,449
  Everything is a scene
  here at the Institute.

772
01:04:15,352 --> 01:04:17,552
  It was designed that way.

773
01:04:19,056 --> 01:04:25,627
  Desmond, suicide was
  Isandra's final fantasy.

774
01:04:26,330 --> 01:04:28,396
  Her final freedom.

775
01:04:28,398 --> 01:04:30,966
  Now, it's regretful,
  but it does happen.

776
01:04:30,968 --> 01:04:34,369
  You didn't suppose that
  the Institute was the only
  mental hospital in the world

777
01:04:34,371 --> 01:04:37,372
  that didn't have its
  percentage of failures?

778
01:04:38,075 --> 01:04:40,075
    Adler failed.

779
01:04:40,077 --> 01:04:41,443
        Jung failed.

780
01:04:42,512 --> 01:04:44,079
      Freud failed!

781
01:04:44,081 --> 01:04:48,483
        But they didn't
        accept failure as
        the ultimate therapy.

782
01:04:48,485 --> 01:04:52,520
                Dr. Quilly,
               you know how long
               I've admired you.

783
01:04:52,522 --> 01:04:54,990
                 We studied your
                books in school,

784
01:04:54,992 --> 01:04:58,026
       we practically worshipped
        at your shrine.

785
01:04:58,028 --> 01:05:01,329
            I came here to learn
              from a great man.

786
01:05:01,331 --> 01:05:04,165
        I'm still trying to
        discover your theories.

787
01:05:04,167 --> 01:05:06,201
          Your real theories.

788
01:05:06,203 --> 01:05:08,536
     Those great books of yours.

789
01:05:08,538 --> 01:05:12,607
  Theoretical books
  put into practice

790
01:05:12,609 --> 01:05:14,709
  are not necessarily
  neat, Desmond.

791
01:05:14,711 --> 01:05:18,179
  A book belongs on a shelf,
  you bring it to life,
  it's no longer a book.

792
01:05:18,181 --> 01:05:19,948
          What is it, Doctor?

793
01:05:23,086 --> 01:05:24,753
      The Institute!

794
01:05:27,057 --> 01:05:28,790
                Doctor.

795
01:05:28,792 --> 01:05:30,258
      (CLEARS THROAT)

796
01:05:30,260 --> 01:05:32,127
            Are you all right?

797
01:05:34,064 --> 01:05:35,430
          Yeah.

798
01:05:36,566 --> 01:05:38,800
  SUSAN: Was it
  bad with Quilly?

799
01:05:38,802 --> 01:05:39,968
                    Yes.

800
01:05:41,071 --> 01:05:42,971
  Must be hard for you.

801
01:05:44,641 --> 01:05:48,944
        Well, for me to have
        had the temerity even
        to question that man...

802
01:05:48,946 --> 01:05:51,046
          Maybe he's
          not that man.

803
01:05:52,249 --> 01:05:55,717
          Please, Susan, that's
          Isandra's story again.

804
01:05:55,719 --> 01:05:59,387
    No, no, I'm not talking
    about Isandra's story.

805
01:05:59,389 --> 01:06:01,323
        I'm just saying
        that people
        sometimes change

806
01:06:01,325 --> 01:06:05,460
    and the Quilly
    that you respected so much
    may be a different one now.

807
01:06:05,462 --> 01:06:08,897
      Some people have
      paid a terrible price
      for greatness.

808
01:06:10,567 --> 01:06:12,634
          Like your Dr. Swanson?

809
01:06:15,072 --> 01:06:16,972
          He could have
          been a great man.

810
01:06:19,776 --> 01:06:24,512
    Susan, there are times
    when I am absolutely
    convinced you are sane.

811
01:06:26,616 --> 01:06:28,283
              Then,

812
01:06:28,285 --> 01:06:31,619
    as yesterday morning,
    that fantasy about
    David's disappearance...

813
01:06:31,621 --> 01:06:33,521
        David was not there!

814
01:06:34,958 --> 01:06:38,226
          All right, Susan,
          anything you say.

815
01:06:39,296 --> 01:06:41,196
  Don't patronize me.

816
01:06:45,168 --> 01:06:46,768
            I was, wasn't I?

817
01:06:46,770 --> 01:06:48,003
        Yes.

818
01:07:26,410 --> 01:07:29,544
          Please don't scream!
          I don't like screams!

819
01:07:32,416 --> 01:07:34,549
              Besides,
              it wouldn't help!

820
01:07:37,154 --> 01:07:41,689
  David, I just saw
  you in your room and
  the door was locked.

821
01:07:41,691 --> 01:07:44,059
              No, it wasn't.

822
01:07:44,061 --> 01:07:47,095
            I was out,
            but after I got
            back to my room

823
01:07:47,097 --> 01:07:49,264
          no one ever came
         to lock the door again.

824
01:07:50,667 --> 01:07:53,334
        No one knows
        that your door
        is unlocked?

825
01:07:53,336 --> 01:07:54,836
            Only the one
            who let me out.

826
01:07:56,440 --> 01:07:59,240
    That is such
    a hard mattress.

827
01:08:01,445 --> 01:08:04,112
    You really should complain.

828
01:08:16,960 --> 01:08:20,528
  David, who let you out?

829
01:08:20,530 --> 01:08:22,864
                 Oh, it's always
                the same person.

830
01:08:25,035 --> 01:08:28,303
          I only like it outside
          for a little while.

831
01:08:28,305 --> 01:08:31,606
        I'm really quite
        comfortable in my room.

832
01:08:31,608 --> 01:08:34,476
       Except when they wash me.

833
01:08:34,478 --> 01:08:37,312
          I used to wash myself.

834
01:08:37,314 --> 01:08:39,481
  You will again.

835
01:08:41,151 --> 01:08:43,251
                    You promise?

836
01:08:43,253 --> 01:08:44,686
            I promise.

837
01:08:49,493 --> 01:08:52,060
              A person should
              wash his own body.

838
01:08:54,598 --> 01:08:56,397
        I think I will.

839
01:09:07,644 --> 01:09:11,513
          I was told to find you
          and kill you!

840
01:09:11,515 --> 01:09:13,982
        But I couldn't kill you.

841
01:09:15,819 --> 01:09:19,521
               Oh, what a lovely
                person you are.

842
01:09:21,992 --> 01:09:25,527
              You remind me
              of someone who was
              very kind to me.

843
01:09:25,529 --> 01:09:27,228
      Nurse Parker.

844
01:09:28,532 --> 01:09:32,400
        She let me wash myself,
        before they killed her.

845
01:09:35,872 --> 01:09:40,542
            They like to
            kill nurses here.
            And doctors, too.

846
01:09:40,544 --> 01:09:44,312
              And they bury them

847
01:09:44,314 --> 01:09:48,883
            in the cellar.

848
01:09:48,885 --> 01:09:53,188
  David, please tell me
  who let you out
  of your room.

849
01:10:03,733 --> 01:10:05,733
          May I have your brush?

850
01:10:09,739 --> 01:10:11,873
                  I'm tired now.

851
01:10:11,875 --> 01:10:13,908
  Do you wanna
  go to your room?

852
01:10:13,910 --> 01:10:15,977
              If you'll take me.

853
01:10:19,015 --> 01:10:20,982
        That was a lovely visit.

854
01:10:28,925 --> 01:10:31,693
  David, where is
  this cellar?

855
01:10:31,695 --> 01:10:34,262
                  Try the old...
          Shh!

856
01:10:34,264 --> 01:10:38,399
              Try the old door
            next to the kitchen.
            Are you going there?

857
01:10:38,401 --> 01:10:41,236
        Maybe.

858
01:10:41,238 --> 01:10:45,173
        I'd invite you in,
        but it's not very tidy.

859
01:10:45,175 --> 01:10:46,841
  That's all right.

860
01:12:02,919 --> 01:12:04,585
          (TOY SQUEAKS)

861
01:12:59,242 --> 01:13:01,109
          It's all in my mind.

862
01:13:51,861 --> 01:13:53,294
                  Hello, Nurse.

863
01:13:53,296 --> 01:13:55,096
          (SIGHS) Luther.

864
01:13:55,098 --> 01:13:57,732
        You're not supposed
       to know about this place,
        neither am I.

865
01:13:57,734 --> 01:13:59,634
      How did you find it?

866
01:13:59,636 --> 01:14:03,204
        Gow showed it to me.
       He knew it would hurt me.

867
01:14:05,308 --> 01:14:08,643
          Come. I have something
          to show you.

868
01:14:14,117 --> 01:14:17,118
        This is Nurse
        Parker's grave.

869
01:14:17,120 --> 01:14:21,389
          I worshipped her.
          She was so kind.

870
01:14:22,659 --> 01:14:25,126
        She looked like you,
        you know.

871
01:14:26,129 --> 01:14:27,895
  How do you know
  that's her grave?

872
01:14:27,897 --> 01:14:31,132
        It's the newest.
        She was the last
        to be killed.

873
01:14:31,134 --> 01:14:32,733
            The last one?

874
01:14:32,735 --> 01:14:35,470
              Dr. Quilly was
              the first to die.

875
01:14:35,472 --> 01:14:38,973
                  He's here.
                  The others
                  are outside.

876
01:14:38,975 --> 01:14:40,641
                  That's the
                real Dr. Quilly?

877
01:14:40,643 --> 01:14:44,846
          Oh, yes.
          The present Quilly
          is a patient.

878
01:14:44,848 --> 01:14:48,916
      He took over
      when Quilly died
      to carry on his work.

879
01:14:48,918 --> 01:14:50,651
       That's what Isandra said.

880
01:14:50,653 --> 01:14:52,687
    Dr. Preisser said
    it was just her fantasy.

881
01:14:52,689 --> 01:14:56,457
  Oh, Preisser's a patient, too.
  We're all patients here,

882
01:14:56,459 --> 01:14:58,292
            except the dead.

883
01:14:58,294 --> 01:15:01,229
      Only the dead are
      sane in the Institute,

884
01:15:03,032 --> 01:15:05,700
          Dr. Moore doesn't know
          anything about this,

885
01:15:05,702 --> 01:15:07,268
                  does he?

886
01:15:08,705 --> 01:15:09,770
                  Does he?

887
01:15:09,772 --> 01:15:10,838
                   LUTHER: Look!

888
01:15:15,812 --> 01:15:19,680
  "Registered Nurse."
  They were nurses, too?

889
01:15:19,682 --> 01:15:21,682
        They bring nurses
        here to the Institute

890
01:15:21,684 --> 01:15:24,719
        so that one of the
        guests can kill them.

891
01:15:24,721 --> 01:15:27,688
        But you don't know
       who's killing the nurses.

892
01:15:27,690 --> 01:15:31,659
      No, I don't know.
      I know they get them here,

893
01:15:31,661 --> 01:15:34,896
      they bring them here
      and they never leave.

894
01:15:34,898 --> 01:15:37,665
          You'll sleep here
          one day, Nurse.

895
01:15:37,667 --> 01:15:40,635
    The candles told me so.

896
01:15:40,637 --> 01:15:43,704
          Oh, Lord God!

897
01:15:43,706 --> 01:15:46,207
        Lord God, vengeance.

898
01:15:46,209 --> 01:15:48,476
            Show thyself!

899
01:16:04,928 --> 01:16:06,494
                    (GASPS)

900
01:16:06,496 --> 01:16:10,598
    Dr. Quilly wants
    to see you now.

901
01:16:10,600 --> 01:16:12,833
               Suppose I say no?

902
01:16:14,337 --> 01:16:18,606
  Then you say no,
  but you will see
  Dr. Quilly now!

903
01:16:18,608 --> 01:16:21,776
            Good! Because I want
              to see him now!

904
01:16:43,533 --> 01:16:45,466
    Soft evening,
    eh, Nurse?

905
01:16:45,468 --> 01:16:49,136
          Almost as if
          all elements conspired

906
01:16:49,138 --> 01:16:51,806
                to quiet the
                beasts in man.

907
01:16:53,977 --> 01:16:55,943
            (SIGHS)

908
01:16:55,945 --> 01:17:00,948
    You are our most
    difficult guest, Nurse.

909
01:17:00,950 --> 01:17:04,285
            Maybe that's because
              I'm not a guest.

910
01:17:04,287 --> 01:17:10,157
    Intense shock therapy
    is the last resort
    of the Institute.

911
01:17:10,159 --> 01:17:13,995
        You have brought me
        to that last resort.

912
01:17:13,997 --> 01:17:16,964
  You were here in my office,
  you used the telephone.

913
01:17:16,966 --> 01:17:18,899
  Oh, don't lie, the operator
  told me all about it.

914
01:17:18,901 --> 01:17:22,970
  You have tried to
  destroy the Institute
  ever since you arrived.

915
01:17:22,972 --> 01:17:26,907
  Then you used dear Ronnie
  to let you in here,

916
01:17:26,909 --> 01:17:31,245
  you flaunted yourself
  in front of David, undoing
  a work of a whole year!

917
01:17:31,247 --> 01:17:34,615
  But the final infamy
  was turning

918
01:17:34,617 --> 01:17:37,752
  Desmond Moore
  from his work, my work!

919
01:17:37,754 --> 01:17:39,620
              Your work?

920
01:17:39,622 --> 01:17:43,090
        Turning a hospital,
        a place of healing
       into a parody of therapy?

921
01:17:44,961 --> 01:17:48,763
        Yes, I was here
        and I used the phone.

922
01:17:48,765 --> 01:17:51,799
      I was also in the cellar.

923
01:17:51,801 --> 01:17:56,003
        You remember the cellar?
          You're buried there,
          so are the nurses.

924
01:17:57,774 --> 01:18:00,274
    (SCREAMING)
    You were in the cellar?

925
01:18:00,276 --> 01:18:02,877
            Yes, and in the
            basement room.

926
01:18:02,879 --> 01:18:05,146
              The one that
              doesn't exist!

927
01:18:05,148 --> 01:18:08,149
      (STAMMERS)
      That's a sacred place!

928
01:18:08,151 --> 01:18:12,119
        No, it's the burial site
          for Dr. Quilly!

929
01:18:12,121 --> 01:18:13,554
              The real one!

930
01:18:13,556 --> 01:18:16,757
        How... How dare you?

931
01:18:18,361 --> 01:18:20,661
          How dare you?

932
01:18:20,663 --> 01:18:23,064
      And this whole damn place!

933
01:18:26,002 --> 01:18:28,569
          This is you, isn't it?

934
01:18:28,571 --> 01:18:32,506
        Paranoid schizophrenic,
        kills nurses.

935
01:18:32,508 --> 01:18:35,209
        You tease and
        kill nurses, don't you?

936
01:18:35,211 --> 01:18:38,079
              You're nothing
              but a patient!

937
01:18:40,750 --> 01:18:44,618
      I am Magnus Quilly.

938
01:18:47,056 --> 01:18:49,857
      This is my hospital.

939
01:18:49,859 --> 01:18:51,459
            Mine!

940
01:18:53,930 --> 01:18:55,763
            (ALARM RINGS)

941
01:18:59,936 --> 01:19:01,602
            (CHOKES)

942
01:19:04,574 --> 01:19:06,474
          (COUGHS)

943
01:19:10,913 --> 01:19:12,446
  Magnus!

944
01:19:13,282 --> 01:19:17,051
  Don't do anything, Doctor.

945
01:19:17,053 --> 01:19:19,220
    I'll call an ambulance,
   we'll have you in Stockton...

946
01:19:19,222 --> 01:19:22,757
  I'll be dead before the
  ambulance can get here.

947
01:19:27,864 --> 01:19:29,897
  It'll be all right, Jones.

948
01:19:29,899 --> 01:19:34,034
  Dr. Moore here
  will look after you.

949
01:19:34,036 --> 01:19:35,803
        (PANTING)

950
01:19:36,606 --> 01:19:39,240
                  Desmond,

951
01:19:39,242 --> 01:19:43,010
          you'll have to
          take command.
          Good luck. Good luck.

952
01:19:46,616 --> 01:19:49,416
            (CHOKING)
            You did this!

953
01:19:49,418 --> 01:19:52,586
    You brought this all on!

954
01:19:52,588 --> 01:19:53,888
            (GRUNTS)

955
01:20:05,935 --> 01:20:07,368
          Is he dead?

956
01:21:00,990 --> 01:21:03,557
          DESMOND: Susan? Susan?

957
01:21:03,559 --> 01:21:05,659
              Are you all right?

958
01:21:05,661 --> 01:21:07,261
                It's Dr. Moore.

959
01:21:10,499 --> 01:21:13,267
          Dr. Quilly is alive.
          I just saw...

960
01:21:16,505 --> 01:21:19,306
  Oh, I'm sorry
  if I startled you.

961
01:21:19,308 --> 01:21:21,775
  It was just to
  honor Dr. Quilly.

962
01:21:30,486 --> 01:21:32,753
            Quite an effective
            performance, Henry.

963
01:21:32,755 --> 01:21:36,156
            Perhaps a bit
            too effective.
            Thank you, Henry.

964
01:21:37,593 --> 01:21:40,561
        Sometimes we see
        things not as they are,

965
01:21:40,563 --> 01:21:42,363
                 but as we would
                like them to be.

966
01:21:42,365 --> 01:21:45,766
            As I mentioned
            to Dr. Paul Swanson
            this morning.

967
01:21:55,378 --> 01:21:57,211
            You're saying you
            spoke with Paul?

968
01:21:57,213 --> 01:21:59,546
        Yes, I called him
        this morning.

969
01:21:59,548 --> 01:22:02,082
          It was sort of
          a hunch really.

970
01:22:02,084 --> 01:22:05,019
        And you'll be
        happy to know
        he's very much alive.

971
01:22:06,222 --> 01:22:07,922
                Alive?

972
01:22:07,924 --> 01:22:10,224
    You weren't his nurse,
    Susan, you were his patient.

973
01:22:10,226 --> 01:22:12,226
        You fell in love
        with him, it seems,

974
01:22:12,228 --> 01:22:15,396
        and because
        of falling in
        love with Paul,

975
01:22:15,398 --> 01:22:18,899
      he felt that
      another doctor should
      take over your treatment.

976
01:22:18,901 --> 01:22:21,735
      The rejection was
      too much for you to bear.

977
01:22:21,737 --> 01:22:25,272
      You imagined him dead
      and ran away

978
01:22:25,274 --> 01:22:27,141
      here to the Institute.

979
01:22:31,981 --> 01:22:33,881
    Maybe I should go back.

980
01:22:33,883 --> 01:22:36,417
          No, of course not.

981
01:22:36,419 --> 01:22:40,387
  The new head of the Institute
  needs a top notch nurse,
  doesn't he?

982
01:22:40,389 --> 01:22:43,223
        I'll be moving
        into my new office.

983
01:22:43,225 --> 01:22:45,459
      Maybe you'd like to help.

984
01:23:01,510 --> 01:23:03,410
              Thank you.

985
01:23:03,412 --> 01:23:07,247
        Needless to say
        the order and serenity

986
01:23:07,249 --> 01:23:10,317
    that Dr. Quilly brought
    to the Institute

987
01:23:10,319 --> 01:23:14,421
      will be one of the most
      important priorities
      during my tenure here.

988
01:23:15,691 --> 01:23:18,559
    Ah, yes, Jones,
    set it right here, please.

989
01:23:21,130 --> 01:23:25,599
  Of course, it'll be
  very important during
  this transition period

990
01:23:25,601 --> 01:23:28,602
  that the rules
  of the Institute
  be strictly obeyed.

991
01:23:30,339 --> 01:23:33,674
  Jones here has
  agreed to stay on
  as head of security

992
01:23:33,676 --> 01:23:36,944
  and help us protect
  our way of life.

993
01:23:36,946 --> 01:23:38,712
        (PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

994
01:23:42,885 --> 01:23:45,219
        Thank you.
        Thank you all.

995
01:24:02,671 --> 01:24:04,805
  Nurse Manning.

996
01:24:04,807 --> 01:24:07,408
  Would you give me
  a hand here, please?

997
01:24:11,414 --> 01:24:15,682
  Nothing like
  a touch of home
  in the office.

998
01:24:15,684 --> 01:24:18,585
  Maybe you can help
  me arrange these.

999
01:24:28,364 --> 01:24:30,564
          (TOY SQUEAKS)

1000
01:24:32,368 --> 01:24:34,168
      I saw a toy like this
      in the basement.

1001
01:24:34,170 --> 01:24:36,603
          It belonged
          to a patient.

1002
01:24:41,877 --> 01:24:47,247
        Paranoid, schizophrenic,
          chemist, teases...

1003
01:24:51,554 --> 01:24:56,623
          He teases.
          He likes toys.
          Kills nurses.

1004
01:24:57,560 --> 01:24:58,959
              (GASPS)

1005
01:25:13,042 --> 01:25:14,808
                  (SCREAMING)

1006
01:25:41,103 --> 01:25:44,071
        (ALARM RINGING)

1007
01:26:04,460 --> 01:26:05,792
  What happened here?

1008
01:26:05,794 --> 01:26:08,829
  There's been an accident.

1009
01:26:08,831 --> 01:26:13,800
  Jones, I want you to
  dispose of the body
  in the usual manner.

1010
01:26:13,802 --> 01:26:17,204
  Ronnie, I want you
  to clean this room up.

1011
01:26:17,206 --> 01:26:19,173
      Yes, Nurse Manning.

1012
01:26:26,015 --> 01:26:27,581
  Donnymead.

1013
01:26:35,524 --> 01:26:38,725
  Donnymead,
  I want you to call a
  staff meeting for later,

1014
01:26:38,727 --> 01:26:42,229
  and I expect everyone
  on the staff to attend.

1015
01:26:42,231 --> 01:26:45,165
                    But... Uh...

1016
01:26:45,167 --> 01:26:46,700
    Do you understand?

1017
01:26:46,702 --> 01:26:48,602
                Uh, yeah.

1018
01:26:53,042 --> 01:26:55,075
            Miss Manning.

1019
01:26:55,077 --> 01:26:57,477
            You must not forget
           you are just a nurse.

1020
01:26:57,479 --> 01:26:59,546
  I'm in charge now.

1021
01:26:59,548 --> 01:27:02,783
  The rest we can discuss
  later at the staff meeting.

1022
01:27:04,486 --> 01:27:05,953
      That's all.

1023
01:27:16,332 --> 01:27:18,765
  Jones, I want you
  to call the driver.

1024
01:27:18,767 --> 01:27:21,168
  The new doctor is
  due to arrive tonight

1025
01:27:21,170 --> 01:27:22,736
  and I'm gonna
  meet him personally.

1026
01:27:22,738 --> 01:27:24,071
            I don't think...

1027
01:27:24,073 --> 01:27:27,174
  No, you don't think!
  I'll do the thinking!

1028
01:27:28,877 --> 01:27:30,310
        Now, go.

1029
01:28:03,379 --> 01:28:05,012
        (CAR HORN HONKS)

1030
01:28:37,413 --> 01:28:38,845
                        Wait!

1031
01:28:59,968 --> 01:29:01,368
        You can't leave.

1032
01:29:02,171 --> 01:29:03,937
                  I'm late!

1033
01:29:03,939 --> 01:29:05,872
    You can't get out.

1034
01:29:06,508 --> 01:29:08,008
                    Why?

1035
01:29:11,613 --> 01:29:14,214
      You need this
      to open the gate.

1036
01:29:18,821 --> 01:29:20,587
            Thank you, Jones.

1037
01:29:33,802 --> 01:29:35,402
    DRIVER: Evening, ma'am.

1038
01:29:36,672 --> 01:29:39,406
        You see? I told you
        you'd get the job.

1039
01:29:41,543 --> 01:29:42,943
            Are you okay?

1040
01:29:44,713 --> 01:29:47,881
              I'm fine.
              Can we please go?

1041
01:29:47,883 --> 01:29:49,616
    The train station, ma'am?

1042
01:29:53,255 --> 01:29:54,988
            Police station.

